{
  "text": "Wikiart is a fine-art paintings dataset first introduced by Saleh et al. [CITATION_1] . The paintings were obtained from the wikiart.org website. Currently, Wikiart is the largest public dataset available that contains around 80,000 annotated paintings for genres, artists and styles classification tasks. However, not all paintings are used in all tasks. To be specific, all paintings are used for 27 styles classification. But, there are only 60,000 paintings annotated for 10 genres, and only around 20,000 paintings are annotated for 23 artists. We released an extended version of Wikiart dataset by randomly splitting the dataset to training and test sets, and this version will be used in our experiments.",
